The paper focuses on wireless networked control systems and proposes an AI-assisted framework for optimizing information latency. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses applications in autonomous driving, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG).
